          * ../app/sys_app/x_casemgmt_case_management.xml and
            ../app/sys_scope/x_casemgmt.xml (scoped application records;
            <sys_scope> and <sys_package> resolve against them by source
            name)
      - This record MUST load BEFORE:
          * ../choices/sys_choice_case_party_party_type.xml (the choice
            values Person, Organization which reference this dictionary
            entry by `name` + `element` lookup against the strings
            `x_casemgmt_case_party` and `party_type`. The two sys_choice
            rows would fail to install if this dictionary entry were
            absent because their name/element foreign-keys would resolve
            to nothing.)
          * ../ui_policy/x_casemgmt_case_party_conditional_fields.xml
            (the UI Policy that drives conditional visibility of the
            person and organization fields based on the value of
            party_type. The UI Policy's condition uses the column name
            `party_type` and would be undefined without this dictionary
            entry. The UI Policy's actions read THIS field's chosen
            value at every form render.)
          * ../seed-data/parties/x_casemgmt_case_party_demo_*.xml (every
            demo party row must specify party_type; the seed data
            would fail to insert if this dictionary record were absent
            because GlideRecord.setValue('party_type', ...) would have
            no target column. AAP Section 0.7.4 mandates "at least one
            Person and one Organization party per demo case" - which by
            definition exercises this column on every demo case.)
          * ../scripts/seed_demo_data.js (the idempotent server-side
            seed script writes synthetic party_type labels via
            GlideRecord.setValue('party_type', ...) for both branches
            of the polymorphism)
          * ../acl/x_casemgmt_case_party_*.xml (table-level ACLs on the
            case_party table; the ACLs reference this column indirectly
            via list-view filters rendered in the auto-generated UI,
            though the table-level ACL conditions themselves do not
            dot-walk through party_type)

    Source for the deterministic sys_id derivation:
        echo -n "x_casemgmt_case_party.party_type" | md5sum
        => 5e02afdbd2f05f407e986015e93d1238

    The MD5 input is the canonical field identifier <name>.<element>,
    matching the same derivation pattern used across all other
    sys_dictionary records in this Update Set.

    Critical naming notes carried forward to
    ../choices/sys_choice_case_party_party_type.xml:
        The two labels are EXACTLY "Person" (capitalized P, 6 chars) and
        "Organization" (capitalized O, American spelling, 12 chars). NOT
        "person" (lowercase), NOT "Persons" (plural), NOT "Organisation"
        (British spelling), NOT "Org" (abbreviated). AAP Section 0.5.7
        verbatim spells the labels "Person, Organization". The Update Set
        re-import gate per AAP Section 0.7.3 will detect any deviation as
        a preview error because the sys_choice rows must reference this
        dictionary entry exactly, AND the UI Policy's condition strings
        ('party_type == "Person"' and 'party_type == "Organization"')
        must match the persisted label exactly.
-->
